# A.8.9 Configuration Management


## Objective

Ensure systems are securely configured, maintained, and changed in a controlled manner.


## Implementation Guidance

•	Define secure baseline configurations (CIS Benchmarks, vendor best practices).
•	Implement version control (Git, Ansible, Puppet).
•	Enforce change management with approvals and rollback plans.
•	Conduct periodic configuration audits.
•	Monitor deviations automatically.


## Audit Criteria

•	Are baselines documented and approved?
•	Are changes logged, reviewed, and approved?
•	Are configuration tools used consistently?
•	Are deviations detected and corrected?
•	Are configuration reviews performed regularly?


## Evidence Examples

•	Baseline documents
•	Change tickets
•	Git commit logs
•	Audit reports
•	Compliance dashboards


## Typical Findings

•	No defined baselines
•	Unauthorized changes
•	Missing rollback plans
•	Manual configuration without version control


## Maturity Indicators

•	Level 1: Manual configuration
•	Level 2: Basic baselines
•	Level 3: Formal change management
•	Level 4: Automated enforcement
•	Level 5: Continuous compliance monitoring


## Related Controls

•	A.5.32 Change Management
•	A.8.8 Vulnerability Management


**Benefits:** Reduces the risk of misconfigurations that could lead to security breaches.
